maxillule. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A</emphasis>
); 0.05 mm (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B, C</emphasis>
); 0.02 mm (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D, E, G</emphasis>
); 0.01 mm(
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">F</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Rostrum not developed. Antennule (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Pusanomyicola sensitivus gen. nov., sp. nov., male A habitus, dorsal B left caudal ramus, dorsal C antennule D antenna E labrum F mandible G maxillule. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (A); 0.05 mm (B, C); 0.02 mm (D, E, G); 0.01 mm (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720736" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">16C</figureCitation>
) 245 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, seven-segmented, densely armed with setae and aesthetascs; armature formula 4+7 aesthetascs, 15+15 aesthetascs, 4+2 aesthetascs, 4+aesthetasc, 2+aesthetasc, and 7+aesthetasc; all setae naked, mostly short; aesthetascs shorter than antennule. Antenna (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Pusanomyicola sensitivus gen. nov., sp. nov., male A habitus, dorsal B left caudal ramus, dorsal C antennule D antenna E labrum F mandible G maxillule. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (A); 0.05 mm (B, C); 0.02 mm (D, E, G); 0.01 mm (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720736" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">16D</figureCitation>
) three-segmented, consisting of coxobasis and two-segmented endopod; coxobasis as long as wide, with one short seta at inner distal corner; first endopodal segment ~ 1.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide, with one small seta at inner subdistal region; second endopodal segment twice longer than wide, terminated in strong claw, armed with five small setae (one on inner margin, one on subdistal outer margin, and three at inner distal corner, one of latter truncate), and ornamented with scattered scale-like spinules on outer surface; terminal claw half as long as second endopodal segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Labrum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Pusanomyicola sensitivus gen. nov., sp. nov., male A habitus, dorsal B left caudal ramus, dorsal C antennule D antenna E labrum F mandible G maxillule. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (A); 0.05 mm (B, C); 0.02 mm (D, E, G); 0.01 mm (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720736" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">16E</figureCitation>
) much wider than long, with patch of several blunt spinules on each lateral surface; posteromedian incision shallow, semicircular, with finely spinulose margin. Mandible (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Pusanomyicola sensitivus gen. nov., sp. nov., male A habitus, dorsal B left caudal ramus, dorsal C antennule D antenna E labrum F mandible G maxillule. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (A); 0.05 mm (B, C); 0.02 mm (D, E, G); 0.01 mm (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720736" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">16F</figureCitation>
) narrowed distally, armed with three armature elements distally: short outer element not articulated at base, with five large teeth along outer margin and five denticles distally; longest middle element (stiff lash) straight, not articulated at base, with several denticles at distal part; slender inner element (spiniform seta) articulated at base, as long as middle element, denticulate distally. Maxillule (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Pusanomyicola sensitivus gen. nov., sp. nov., male A habitus, dorsal B left caudal ramus, dorsal C antennule D antenna E labrum F mandible G maxillule. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (A); 0.05 mm (B, C); 0.02 mm (D, E, G); 0.01 mm (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720736" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">16G</figureCitation>
) as digitiform lobe tipped with two unequal, naked setae. Maxilla (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Pusanomyicola sensitivus gen. nov. sp. nov., male A maxilla B maxilliped C leg 1 D leg 2 E leg 3 F leg 4 G leg 5 H right genital operculum, ventral. Scale bars: 0.02 mm (A, B, G); 0.05 mm (C-F, H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720737" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17A</figureCitation>
) as tapering, unsegmented lobe bearing patch of spinules on posteroventral surface, tipped with one naked seta. Maxilliped (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Pusanomyicola sensitivus gen. nov. sp. nov., male A maxilla B maxilliped C leg 1 D leg 2 E leg 3 F leg 4 G leg 5 H right genital operculum, ventral. Scale bars: 0.02 mm (A, B, G); 0.05 mm (C-F, H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720737" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17B</figureCitation>
) four-segmented; first segment (syncoxa) broader than long, unarmed; second segment (basis) rectangular, armed with one broad, leaf-like seta subdistally and one small seta distally; short third segment (first endopodal segment) unarmed; terminal segment (second endopodal segment) tapering, curved, trifurcate at tip, with one small seta on inner margin; claw or hook absent (or reduced to small middle process of distal tip).
</paragraph>
