<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Legs 1-4 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Pusanomyicola sensitivus gen. nov. sp. nov., male A maxilla B maxilliped C leg 1 D leg 2 E leg 3 F leg 4 G leg 5 H right genital operculum, ventral. Scale bars: 0.02 mm (A, B, G); 0.05 mm (C-F, H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720737" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17C-F</figureCitation>
) biramous, with three-segmented rami; inner coxal seta small, naked; outer seta on basis also small, naked; both rami of each leg almost equal in length; spines on exopods and endopods spinulose along both margins. Leg 1 lacking inner distal element of basis, but with three blunt dentiform spinules near base of endopod. Legs 3 and 4 with same armature on third exopodal segment. Armature formula for legs 1-4 as follows:
</paragraph>
